  "text": "As seen in Figure 4 , the P3 for easy targets has a significantly larger amplitude than the P3 for hard targets [F(1, 10) = 9.65, MSE = 2.1, p = .011]. The mean amplitude in the 300-600 msec posttarget area is 9.7 AV (SEM = 1.1) for easy targets and 7.8 AV (SEM = 1.4) for hard targets. Although the P3 for hard targets starts slightly later than the P3 for easy targets, it also returns back to baseline more rapidly, thus, the small difference in 50% area latency analysis [CITATION_1] ) is nonsignificant [easy targets: mean = 464 msec (SEM = 8) vs. hard targets: mean = 469 msec (SEM = 13); F(1, 10) = 0.55, MSE = 241, p = .476].",
